 barrier Maurice wandered, the wrong words on his lips and the wrong desires in his heart, and his arms full of air.\n\n- E.M.\n|\n...it is not enough to be freeof the whips, principalities and powers\n\n- Edward Kamau Brathwaite, The Arrivants: A New World Trilogy\n|\nThe hallway felt like time itself, and Patricia Buckingham and I were standing at opposite ends-her looking back on all she'd seen, me wondering what lay ahead.\n\n- Ally Carter, Don't Judge a Girl by Her Cover\n|\nIf you don't like the place where you find yourself, Waldemar, it pays to remember that you'll be somewhere else in just a moment. The place itself will be a different place.\n\n- John Wray, The Lost Time Accidents\n|\nWhen in doubt, do what they do in books, was one of Gabriel's secret mottos and - that rarest of things - a principle that he actually lived by.\n\n- Jean-Christophe Valtat, Luminous Chaos\n|\nWhomsoever embraces their creativity along with their individuality, embraces all possibility deep within.\n\n- H.L. Balcomb, Cinderella In Focus: 'Curiosity is the doorway to our personal possibility!' 2nd Edition coming Oct.  31, 2017\n|\nIf I breathe, what will my heart think?If I vomit, what will my soul think?\n\n- Xi Chuan, Notes on the Mosquito: Selected Poems\n|\nWe are powerful beyond measure,and we must stand powerfully in the face of injustice and hate.United.\n\n- Scott\n|\nThis was all in the making, a long time ago. You had as much control over these events as a leaf does in the time of its falling.\n\n- Colin\n|\nNoble though it may be, our way of life is nothing but servitude. It does not take long for servitude to turn to subjugation.– Shikandin Draupada\n\n- Krishna Udayasankar, Kurukshetra\n|\nDeath has his favorites, like anyone. Those who are beloved of Death will not die.\n\n- Holly Black, The Coldest Girl in Coldtown\n|\nYour destiny grows clearer, Jason Grace. When the choice comes again- storm or fire- remember me. And do not despair.\n\n- Rick Riordan, The House of Hades\n|\nYou learn in this business: It you want a friend, get a dog.\n\n- Carl\n|\nAn eleven-year-old girl is many things, but she is not stupid.\n\n- Markus Zusak, The Book Thief\n|\nI never lie. I believe everything I say, so it's not a lie.\n\n- Mark\n|\nWhen you are content to be simply yourself and don't compare or compete, everyone will respect you.\n\n- Lao Tzu, Tao Te Ching\n|\nProofs are to mathematics what spelling (or even calligraphy) is to poetry. Mathematical works do consist of proofs, just as poems do consist of words.\n\n- V.I.\n|\nEverything around you that you call life was made up by people, and you can change it.\n\n- Steve\n|\nThe mind has a powerful way of attracting things that are in harmony with it, good and bad.\n\n- Idowu Koyenikan, Wealth for All: Living a Life of Success at the Edge of Your Ability\n|\nHow could I choose someone who would force me to give up my own small reach for meaning? I chose myself, and without consolation.\n\n- Sue Monk Kidd, The Invention of Wings\n|\nThe mind is not a book, to be opened at will and examined at leisure.\n\n- J.K.\n|\nMost of my kin are bastards,' [Tyrion] said with a wry smile, 'but you're the first I've had to friend.\n\n- George R.R. Martin, A Game of Thrones\n|\nMy body is like breakfast, lunch, and dinner. I don't think about it, I just have it.\n\n- Arnold\n|\nSee? Memories aren't happy, they're sad. Don't you know anything?\n\n- Morris\n|\nPeople may not see you the way you see yourself. But, that's because they don't want to acknowledge your uniqueness. Jealousy is not disguised.\n\n- Amaka Imani Nkosazana, Sweet Destiny\n|\nSaadi: Be a true renouncer, (zahid) and [you can even] ware satin.\n\n- Idries Shah, Sufi Thought and Action\n|\nIf an evil spirit had to hide from God, it would hide in a diamond. If an angel had to hide from the Devil, it would hide in rose quartz.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nIf you must speak ill of another, 